    { "term": "Section 35", "definition": "A part of the 1982 Constitution that says 'The existing aboriginal and treaty rights of the aboriginal peoples of Canada are hereby recognized and affirmed.' It is the strongest protection for Indigenous rights in the country." },
    { "term": "UNDRIP", "definition": "The United Nations Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples. It is an international agreement that sets the standard for how governments should treat Indigenous communities." },
    { "term": "Moderate Livelihood", "definition": "A legal standard defined by the Supreme Court. It means earning enough to pay for food, clothing, housing, and basic comforts, but it does not mean 'unlimited wealth'." },
